author: Scott Ellis
title: Five shows you shouldn't miss: October 22 - 29, 2015
text:
Kitchen Cabinet's Annabel Crabb. 
Ready for This 
Monday, ABC3, 5.30pm 
The kids are still trying to find their way at Arcadia House, but it turns out Reece (Christian Byers) has a very different reason to be there than the others.
Advertisement Kitchen Cabinet 
Wednesday, ABC, 8pm 
Annabel Crabb returns for another revealing look at our politicians, this week chatting with Scott Morrison about immigration, tough choices and how to make samosas.
Blindspot 
Wednesday, Seven, 8.30pm 
Australian Sullivan Stapleton stars as an FBI agent facing the ultimate mystery â€“ a woman with no memory, but a body covered in tattoos that lead to criminals.
Jamie's Super Foods 
Thursday, Ten, 7.30pm 
Yes, we've seen him in a thousand other series, but there's no denying Jamie Oliver's passion for food and in this case, how the right foods can change lives for the better.
Generation Kill 
Available now, Presto 
From The Wire creator David Simon comes HBO's revealing look at American troops on the ground during 2003 invasion of Iraq and how they coped (or not) with their war.
